Text.Value: Ignorance is agony, my friend. I will include you in my prayers. I'd better get started - for your sake.
Nettie's your best bet, with Master Halsin gone. She should be with the others in the inner chambers.
You don't know Kagha. She won't listen. I'm truly sorry.
What do you mean?
I know it's drastic, but more monsters seem to terrorise this region every day.
I'm looking for a healer.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: TODO: add tag to check if halsin isn't back yet

Text.Value: There just aren't enough supplies to support everyone.
We druids will be safe. As for those that took refuge here... well, may Silvanus guard them as they continue their travels.
I pray to Silvanus each night - the Wild Father will protect those refugees. I hope.
Always happy to help those who follow the First Circle.
Of course. But please remember: you're not the only one in need.
Seems like most are tieflings. They'll be fine. They have devilish powers.
Your prayers won't save them. But your voice might sway Kagha.
So you're really locking down the grove?
But you'll need to be quick - the ritual will be complete before too long.
Another outsider? This place has certainly become popular.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Arron turns around and wipes his hands on his trousers (he was standing at a table, with his back to the player).

Text.Value: Nettie could put you to rights. She should be with the others in the inner chambers, but I doubt she'll be taking on new patients. The grove will be locked down soon.
As I said, it's a drastic measure. But the survival of the grove is paramount.
A drastic measure. But more monsters seem to terrorise this region every day.
I can do nothing but pray to Silvanus in the hopes that He'll protect them.
You sound just like Kagha. Oh, that it had to come to this...
I pray no goblin arrow has grazed you!
I'd like to see your wares.
Silvanus be with you.
None will be able to enter - or leave.
Ah - I forgot you're a blow-in. A few days hence, this grove will be completely concealed by thorny vines.
Silvanus guide your path.
Casting out the tieflings. Original.
Dire times. High stakes. I understand.
Are you really locking down the grove?
Refugees, adventurers, and even a drow! No one in years and suddenly we're overwhelmed.
Refugees, adventurers, and now a far-out visitor! No one in years and suddenly we're overwhelmed.
Refugees, adventurers, and even a duergar! No one in years and suddenly we're overwhelmed.
Refugees, adventurers - no one in years and suddenly we're overwhelmed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Arron turns around and wipes his hands on his trousers (he was standing at a table, with his back to the player).

Text.Value: What about the people here?
You just said the region's overrun by monsters. They won't survive by themselves.
Need anything else?
Is there anything you need? I lower my prices for fellow druids.
What are you selling?
Just some bits and bobs I no longer need.
Leave.
Is there anything you need? Act fast if you do - the ritual will be complete before too long.
I don't want this to happen either, but Kagha makes the decisions.
Well met, and thank you for beating back those goblins. Most brave of you.
What ritual are you talking about?

Synopsis: Arron is a friendly, but tired servant to the druids in the grove. Unless the player is a druid, he would rather they don't linger, though he is sympathetic and will help them any way he can (by selling them supplies). He is happy to see a druid and to help them. He can be a little preachy.
